[SN]TITLE[SN]
Men charged over Hinterland actor Aneirin Hughes attack

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three men have been charged after Hinterland actor Aneirin Hughes was attacked outside a pub.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
A 52-year-old was charged with assault by beating, a 24-year-old with assault by beating and causing actual bodily harm, and a 40-year-old with assault causing actual bodily harm and being drunk and disorderly.
The alleged incident took place outside Rummers Wine Bar, Aberystwyth, in July.
The men will appear at Aberystwyth Magistrates' Court on 4 January.
Mr Hughes plays Chf Supt Brian Prosser in the BBC Wales bilingual drama.
